<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Get up and running with k9s on k9s Documentation PREVIEW</title><link>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/</link><description>Recent content in Get up and running with k9s on k9s Documentation PREVIEW</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Installation</title><link>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/installation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/installation/</guid><description>&lt;p>K9s is available on Linux, macOS and Windows platforms.
Binaries for Linux, Windows and Mac are available as tarballs in the &lt;a href="https://github.com/derailed/k9s/releases">release page&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="macos">MacOS&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="homebrew">Homebrew&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Via &lt;a href="https://brew.sh/">Homebrew&lt;/a> for macOS or Linux&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>brew install derailed/k9s/k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="macports">MacPorts&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Via &lt;a href="https://www.macports.org">MacPorts&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>sudo port install k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="linux">Linux&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="snap">Snap&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Via &lt;a href="https://snapcraft.io/k9s">snap&lt;/a> for Linux&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>snap install k9s --devmode
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="arch">Arch&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>On Arch Linux&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>pacman -S k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="opensuse">OpenSUSE&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>On OpenSUSE Linux distribution&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>zypper install k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="bsd">BSD&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>On FreeBSD&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>pkg install k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="windows">Windows&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="winget">Winget&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>&lt;a href="https://github.com/microsoft/winget-cli">Winget&lt;/a> for Windows&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Running with Docker</title><link>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/docker/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/docker/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="running-with-docker">Running with Docker&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="running-the-official-docker-image">Running the official Docker image&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>You can run k9s as a Docker container by mounting your &lt;code>KUBECONFIG&lt;/code>:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>docker run --rm -it -v $KUBECONFIG:/root/.kube/config quay.io/derailed/k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>For default path it would be:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>docker run --rm -it -v ~/.kube/config:/root/.kube/config quay.io/derailed/k9s
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="building-your-own-docker-image">Building your own Docker image&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>You can build your own Docker image of k9s from the &lt;a href="Dockerfile">Dockerfile&lt;/a> with the following:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>docker build -t k9s-docker:v0.0.1 .
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>You can get the latest stable &lt;code>kubectl&lt;/code> version and pass it to the &lt;code>docker build&lt;/code> command with the &lt;code>--build-arg&lt;/code> option.
You can use the &lt;code>--build-arg&lt;/code> option to pass any valid &lt;code>kubectl&lt;/code> version (like &lt;code>v1.18.0&lt;/code> or &lt;code>v1.19.1&lt;/code>).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Learn how to configure k9s</title><link>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/getting-started/configuration/</guid><description>&lt;p>An extended configuration guide can be found at &lt;a href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/configuration/">Configuration&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>You can also jump right-into a specific topic such as:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Styling k9s with &lt;a href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/configuration/skins/">Skins&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Be faster with resource &lt;a href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/configuration/aliases/">Aliases&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Per-cluster settings via &lt;a href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/configuration/cluster/">Cluster settings&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Custom keyboard shortcuts via &lt;a href="https://k9sdoc.keg.im/docs/configuration/hotkeys/">Hotkeys&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul></description></item></channel></rss>